'''Abu Yahya ibn Abd al-Haqq''' (died 1258?) was a [[Marinid]] ruler. He was the son of [[Abd al-Haqq I]] and the brother of both [[Uthman ibn Abd al-Haqq|Uthman I]] and [[Muhammad ibn Abd Al-Haqq|Muhammad I]]. During his time as leader of the Marinids, they capture and make Fès their capital. The Almohads attempt a retaliatory strike against the Marinids but it is not successful.

