'''Gerhard Vilhelm Jynge''' (1877 – February 21, 1945) was a [[Norwegians|Norwegian]] newspaper editor.

He became the editor of ''[[Oplandenes Avis]]'' in 1908<ref name="Hoeg">Høeg, Tom Arbo. 1974. ''Norske aviser: Registerbind''. Oslo: Universitetsbibliotekets Hustrykkeri, p. 179.</ref> and the sub-editor of ''[[Verdens Gang]]'' in 1911, served as the first editor of ''[[Haugesunds-Pressen|Haugesunds Dagblad]]'' from June 8, 1912 to December 1913,<ref name="Hoeg"/> became the editor of ''[[Dagsposten]]'' in [[Trondheim]] in 1914,<ref name="Hoeg"/> and was the editor of ''[[Aalesunds Avis]]'' from 1917 to 1921.<ref name="Hoeg"/><ref>Diesen, Emil. 1921. ''Norske aviser og tidsskrifter med fortegnelse over norske pressefolk 1920''. Kristiania, p. 19.</ref> He became an appellate judge pro tem{{clarify|date=April 2017}} in Bergen in 1921, and a regular judge in 1928. He died on February 21, 1945, when the steamship ''Austri'' was sunk by British aircraft in [[Bømlafjorden|Bømla Fjord]].<ref>[https://digitaltmuseum.no/011085442900/det-gamle-skatollet ''DigitaltMuseum'': Det gamle skatollet.]</ref><ref>[http://www.bt.no/nyheter/innenriks/Kystruta-skoten-i-senk-av-sine-eigne-297961b.html Olderkjær, Ove A. 2015. Kystruta skoten i senk av sine eigne. ''Bergens Tidende'' (February 20).]</ref>

