{{Infobox person | name = Nick Mennell | image = Nick Mennell.jpg | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1976}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Actor | years_active = 1998–present | education = [[Juilliard School]] {{small|([[Bachelor of Fine Arts|BFA]])}} }} '''Nick Mennell''' is an [[United States|American]] [[actor]] known for his stage work as well as his roles in the [[Horror film|horror]]/[[slasher film|slasher]] remakes of ''[[Halloween (2007 film)|Halloween]]'', and ''[[Friday the 13th (2009 film)|Friday the 13th]]''.
==Life and career==
Mennell graduated from [[Juilliard School]] in 2005.
In 2007, Mennell was cast as Bob Simms, in the [[Halloween (2007 film)|remake]] of the 1978 [[John Carpenter]] classic ''[[Halloween (1978 film)|Halloween]]''. The film was directed by [[Rob Zombie]], and starred [[Scout Taylor-Compton]], [[Danielle Harris]], [[Malcolm McDowell]], and [[Tyler Mane]] as [[Michael Myers (Halloween)|Michael Myers]]. The film opened on August 31, 2007, and debut at number one at the box office.
In 2008, Mennell was cast as Mike in the 2009 version of ''[[Friday the 13th (2009 film)|Friday the 13th]]'' and was directed by [[Marcus Nispel]]. The film also starred [[Amanda Righetti]], [[Jared Padalecki]], [[Danielle Panabaker]], and [[Derek Mears]] as [[Jason Voorhees]].<ref>[http://www.bloody-disgusting.com/news/19613 Two TV Spots, EPK for 'The Black Waters of Echo's Pond']</ref> The film opened on February 13, 2009, and debuted at number one at the box office. He stars also in the 2009 shot Fantasy horror film ''[[The Black Waters of Echo's Pond]]'', which is directed by Gabriel Bologna.<ref>[http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/36174/the-black-waters-echos-pond-roll-a-limited-theatrical-release The Black Waters of Echo's Pond Roll into a Limited Theatrical Release]</ref>
