'''William ("Billy") Brown''' (17 January 1889 – unknown) was an English [[cricket]]er active from 1919 to 1923 who played for [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]]. He was born in [[Accrington]]; details of his death are unknown. He appeared in ten [[first-class cricket|first-class matches]]. It is not known if he was right or lefthanded, but he [[bowling (cricket)|bowled]] at [[fast bowling|fast medium pace]]. He scored 239 [[run (cricket)|runs]] with a highest score of 39 and held ten catches. He took 22 [[wicket]]s with a best analysis of four for 22.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/28/28216/28216.html Billy Brown at CricketArchive]</ref>

